9. Use Container Widget with padding property in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Container widget in Flutter uses the padding property to add space inside the container, between its border and its child widget.

Padding is defined using EdgeInsets
It improves readability and layout spacing
Unlike margin, padding works inside the contain

//main code


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ContainerPaddingExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ContainerPaddingExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Container Padding Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Container(
          padding: EdgeInsets.all(20),
          height: 120,
          width: 220,
          color: Colors.purple,
          child: Text(
            "With Padding",
            style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 18),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
